-- Argentina Raising Minimum Threshold for Incomes Taxes by 20%, Boudou Says
-- Silvia Martinez
-- 2010-07-08T17:26:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/argentina-raising-minimum-threshold-for-incomes-taxes-by-20-boudou-says.html

          
          
             Argentina is raising the minimum
threshold for income taxes by about 20 percent, a move that will
cost the government 3.2 billion pesos ($810 million) in revenue,
Economy Minister Amado Boudou said today in Buenos Aires.  
 The income tax change is effective as of July 1, Boudou
said.  
